<paragraph blockId="1.[151,655,151,178]" box="[151,655,151,178]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,655,151,178]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,655,151,178]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">
<taxonomicName authorityName="M'Coy" authorityYear="1847" box="[151,340,151,177]" class="Trilobita" family="Brachymetopidae" genus="Brachymetopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Proetida" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,340,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Brachymetopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Permian of 
<collectingCountry box="[572,655,152,178]" name="Russia" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Russia</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,222,463]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Permian brachymetopids are rare compared with proetoideans, and are known from only eight Russian localities (including that described in this paper).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="348" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,222,463]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">
A cephalon of a species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M'Coy" authorityYear="1847" box="[525,699,294,319]" class="Trilobita" family="Brachymetopidae" genus="Brachymetopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Proetida" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[525,699,294,319]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Brachymetopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from near the village of Zlatoust (now the village of Klyuchi, Suksun Region, 
<collectingRegion box="[334,393,331,354]" country="Russia" name="Perm'" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Perm</collectingRegion>
Krai, 
<collectingCountry box="[462,538,330,355]" name="Russia" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Russia</collectingCountry>
) was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Moller, V. von" box="[750,901,330,355]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" pagination="1 - 81" refId="ref7240" refString="Moller, V. von (1867) Uber die Trilobiten der Steinkohlenformation des Urals, nebst einer Uebersicht und einigen Erganzungen der bisherigen Beobachtungen uber Kohlen Trilobiten im Allgemeinen. Bulletin of the Imperial Society of Naturalists of Moscow, 1, 1 - 81. [in German]" type="journal article" year="1867">Möller (1867</bibRefCitation>
, pp. 184–187, Pl. 2, figs. 32–35; 1868, p. 57, Pl. 1, figs 32–35; 
<figureCitation box="[321,401,366,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1158,1180]" captionTargetBox="[415,1172,515,1136]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[415,1172,515,1136]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Some members of the genus Brachymetopus from the Permian of Russia. a—B. (Acutimetopus) moelleri (Weber, 1932); reconstruction of cephalon; presumably kept (possibly lost) in the collections of the St. Petersburg Mining University museum, St. Petersburg; Lower Permian, Artinskian, Sarginian (reproduced from Möller [1868, Pl. 1, Fig. 32]). b, c—B. (Conimetopus) alekseevi Mychko, sp. nov.; b—cephalon, spec. TsNIGR no. 5107/2063; c—pygidium, spec. TsNIGR no. 5107/ 2064; Chelyabinsk Region, Ashinsky District, right bank of the Sim River, the town of Asha, “Kazarmenny Kamen” locality; Lower Permian, Asselian; (reproduced from Weber [1937, Pl. 10, figs 10–11]). d, e—B. (Acutimetopus) caucasicus Likharev, 1944; spec. TsNIGR no. 5217/86, holotype, pygidium; Krasnodar Region, Mostovsky District, the Malaya Laba River basin, “Nikitinskaya Balka” locality; Upper Permian, Dzhulfian (~Wuchiapingian), Urushten or Nikitin Formations; d—view from the dorsal side, e—view from the end of the posterior margin (reproduced from Weber [1944, Pl 2, Fig. 15]). The scale bar is 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624469/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
herein). The stratigraphic unit in which the cephalon was found belongs to the Sarginian horizon of the Early Permian (Artinskian; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mychko, E. V. &amp; Alekseev, A. S." box="[621,943,402,427]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" pagination="40 - 83" refId="ref7190" refString="Mychko, E. V. &amp; Alekseev, A. S. (2017) Localities of middle Carboniferous-Permian trilobites in Russia and surrounding countries. Bulletin of Moscow Society of Naturalists. Geological Series, 92 (3), 40 - 83. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="2017">Mychko and Alekseev, 2017</bibRefCitation>
, p. 58). 
<bibRefCitation author="Hahn, G. &amp; Hahn, R." box="[1031,1286,402,427]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" pagination="1 - 242" refId="ref6556" refString="Hahn, G. &amp; Hahn, R. (1996) Die trilobiten-taxa des Karbons und Perms 2. Brachymetopidae. Courier Forschungsinstitut Senckenberg, 195, 1 - 242. [in German]" type="journal article" year="1996">Hahn and Hahn (1996)</bibRefCitation>
assigned this specimen to the Asselian 
<taxonomicName authority="Weber, 1932" authorityName="Weber" authorityYear="1932" box="[437,1041,438,463]" class="Trilobita" family="Brachymetopidae" genus="Brachymetopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Proetida" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moelleri" subGenus="Acutimetopus">
<emphasis box="[437,611,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Brachymetopus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[628,780,439,462]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Acutimetopus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[796,889,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">moelleri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Weber, V. N." box="[896,1041,438,463]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" pagination="1 - 157" refId="ref8047" refString="Weber, V. N. (1932) Trilobity Turkestana. Trudy Vsesoyuznogo Geologo-Razvedochnogo Ob'edineniya N. K. T. P-S. S. S. R, 178, 1 - 157. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1932">Weber, 1932</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624469/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" startId="1.[151,250,1158,1180]" targetBox="[415,1172,515,1136]" targetPageId="1">
