<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1501,2030]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,501]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="348" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">
<bibRefCitation author="Krasnopolsky, A. A." box="[199,521,1501,1526]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" pagination="267 - 303" refId="ref6820" refString="Krasnopolsky, A. A. (1887) Kratkiy ocherk geologicheskogo stroyeniya Kynovskoy dachi na Urale. Izvestia Geologicheskogo kommiteta, 6, 267 - 303. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1887">Krasnopolsky (1887, p. 295)</bibRefCitation>
reported a trilobite specimen identified as &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Vern." authorityName="Vern." box="[1015,1361,1501,1526]" class="Trilobita" family="Brachymetopidae" genus="Brachymetopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Proetida" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uralicus">
<emphasis box="[1015,1289,1501,1526]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Brachymetopus uralicus</emphasis>
Vern.
</taxonomicName>
,&quot; from near the village Kyn on the Talca River, 
<collectingRegion box="[625,684,1538,1561]" country="Russia" name="Perm'" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Perm</collectingRegion>
Region, 
<collectingCountry box="[791,869,1537,1562]" name="Russia" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Russia</collectingCountry>
. The age of this specimen is unknown and could potentially range from Middle Carboniferous to Early Permian (
<bibRefCitation author="Mychko, E. V. &amp; Alekseev, A. S." box="[866,1261,1573,1598]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" pagination="40 - 83" refId="ref7190" refString="Mychko, E. V. &amp; Alekseev, A. S. (2017) Localities of middle Carboniferous-Permian trilobites in Russia and surrounding countries. Bulletin of Moscow Society of Naturalists. Geological Series, 92 (3), 40 - 83. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="2017">Mychko and Alekseev, 2017, p. 56</bibRefCitation>
). Subsequently, from the rocky outcrop of the Upper Carboniferous—Lower Permian limestone reef “Kamen Plakun” on the Chusovaya River, Krasnopolsky (1889, p. 221) reported a specimen also identified as &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Vern." authorityName="Vern." class="Trilobita" family="Brachymetopidae" genus="Brachymetopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Proetida" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uralicus">
<emphasis box="[1160,1436,1645,1670]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Brachymetopus uralicus</emphasis>
Vern.
</taxonomicName>
&quot; No images of these specimens were published and their precise age is unknown. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Hahn, G. &amp; Hahn, R." pageId="1" pageNumber="347" pagination="1 - 242" refId="ref6556" refString="Hahn, G. &amp; Hahn, R. (1996) Die trilobiten-taxa des Karbons und Perms 2. Brachymetopidae. Courier Forschungsinstitut Senckenberg, 195, 1 - 242. [in German]" type="journal article" year="1996">Hahn and Hahn's (1996, p. 114)</bibRefCitation>
revision, the species 
<taxonomicName authority="(de Verneuil, 1845)" authorityName="de Verneuil" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="de Verneuil" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[628,1160,1717,1742]" class="Trilobita" family="Brachymetopidae" genus="Brachymetopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Proetida" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ouralicus" subGenus="Conimetopus">
<emphasis box="[628,645,1718,1741]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">B</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[668,816,1718,1741]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Conimetopus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[832,937,1717,1742]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">ouralicus</emphasis>
(de 
<bibRefCitation author="Verneuil, E. de" box="[986,1151,1717,1742]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" pagination="15 - 396" refId="ref7960" refString="Verneuil, E. de (1845) Terrain Paleozoique. Animaux. In: Murchison, R. I., de Verneuil E. &amp; Keyserling, A. (Eds.), G eologie de la Russie d'Europe et des montagnes de l'Oural. Vol. II. Troiseme partie. Paleontologie. J. Murray, London, Bertrand, Paris, pp. 15 - 396. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 121912" type="book chapter" year="1845">Verneuil, 1845</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is known from the Early and Middle Carboniferous (
<figureCitation box="[489,567,1753,1778]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1956,1978]" captionText="FIGURE 4. Stratigraphic distribution of species of Brachymetopus (Conimetopus)." pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Krasnopolsky's (
<bibRefCitation author="Krasnopolsky, A. A." box="[792,852,1753,1777]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" pagination="267 - 303" refId="ref6820" refString="Krasnopolsky, A. A. (1887) Kratkiy ocherk geologicheskogo stroyeniya Kynovskoy dachi na Urale. Izvestia Geologicheskogo kommiteta, 6, 267 - 303. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1887">1887</bibRefCitation>
, 1889) specimens are unlikely to belong to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="de Verneuil" baseAuthorityYear="1845" class="Trilobita" family="Brachymetopidae" genus="Brachymetopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Proetida" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ouralicus" subGenus="Conimetopus">
<emphasis box="[1412,1429,1754,1777]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">B</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[160,308,1790,1813]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Conimetopus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[327,433,1789,1814]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">ouralicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Weber, V. N." box="[449,682,1789,1814]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" pagination="1 - 104" refId="ref8087" refString="Weber, V. N. (1937) Trilobity kamennougolnych i permskich otlozenij SSSR. Vypusk 1. Kamennougolnye trilobity. Monografii popaleontologii SSSR, 71, 1 - 104. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1937">Weber (1937, p. 84)</bibRefCitation>
assigned a trilobite cephalon and pygidium (
<figureCitation box="[1206,1319,1789,1814]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1158,1180]" captionTargetBox="[415,1172,515,1136]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[415,1172,515,1136]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Some members of the genus Brachymetopus from the Permian of Russia. a—B. (Acutimetopus) moelleri (Weber, 1932); reconstruction of cephalon; presumably kept (possibly lost) in the collections of the St. Petersburg Mining University museum, St. Petersburg; Lower Permian, Artinskian, Sarginian (reproduced from Möller [1868, Pl. 1, Fig. 32]). b, c—B. (Conimetopus) alekseevi Mychko, sp. nov.; b—cephalon, spec. TsNIGR no. 5107/2063; c—pygidium, spec. TsNIGR no. 5107/ 2064; Chelyabinsk Region, Ashinsky District, right bank of the Sim River, the town of Asha, “Kazarmenny Kamen” locality; Lower Permian, Asselian; (reproduced from Weber [1937, Pl. 10, figs 10–11]). d, e—B. (Acutimetopus) caucasicus Likharev, 1944; spec. TsNIGR no. 5217/86, holotype, pygidium; Krasnodar Region, Mostovsky District, the Malaya Laba River basin, “Nikitinskaya Balka” locality; Upper Permian, Dzhulfian (~Wuchiapingian), Urushten or Nikitin Formations; d—view from the dorsal side, e—view from the end of the posterior margin (reproduced from Weber [1944, Pl 2, Fig. 15]). The scale bar is 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624469/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Fig. 1b, c</figureCitation>
) from the locality “Kazarmenny Kamen” in the Southern Urals (now “Kazarmenny Greben”, 
<collectingRegion box="[1088,1228,1825,1850]" country="Russia" name="Chelyabinsk" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Chelyabinsk</collectingRegion>
Region, Ashinsky District, the right bank of the Sim River near the Asha town) to the species now classified as 
<taxonomicName authority="Weber, 1932" authorityName="Weber" authorityYear="1932" class="Trilobita" family="Brachymetopidae" genus="Brachymetopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Proetida" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moelleri" subGenus="Acutimetopus">
<emphasis box="[1262,1436,1861,1886]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Brachymetopus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[160,312,1898,1921]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Acutimetopus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[329,422,1897,1922]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">moelleri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Weber, V. N." box="[429,573,1897,1922]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" pagination="1 - 157" refId="ref8047" refString="Weber, V. N. (1932) Trilobity Turkestana. Trudy Vsesoyuznogo Geologo-Razvedochnogo Ob'edineniya N. K. T. P-S. S. S. R, 178, 1 - 157. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1932">Weber, 1932</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Weber, V. N." box="[584,737,1897,1922]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" pagination="1 - 104" refId="ref8087" refString="Weber, V. N. (1937) Trilobity kamennougolnych i permskich otlozenij SSSR. Vypusk 1. Kamennougolnye trilobity. Monografii popaleontologii SSSR, 71, 1 - 104. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1937">Weber (1937)</bibRefCitation>
considered this locality Late Carboniferous. However, the age of “Kazarmenny Greben,” which is a large Bryozoan-Tubiphytes boundstone (
<bibRefCitation author="Tolstikhina, M. M." box="[1128,1338,1933,1958]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" pagination="1 - 177" refId="ref7915" refString="Tolstikhina, M. M. (1941) Karbon i nizhnyaya perm' vostoka Russkoy platformy i zapadnogo sklona Urala. In: Trudy Bashkirskogo geologicheskogo upravleniya. Vol. 11. Gosgeolizdat Moscow-Leningrad, pp. 1 - 177. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1941">Tolstikhina, 1941</bibRefCitation>
, p. 73; 
<bibRefCitation author="Miloradovich, B. V. &amp; Ilina, N. S." box="[151,474,1969,1994]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" refId="ref7014" refString="Miloradovich, B. V. &amp; Ilina, N. S. (1951) Litolgo-paleontologicheskaya kharakteristika kamennougol'nykh i nizhnepermskikh otlozheniy Priural'ya. Gostoptekhizdat, Moscow-Leningrad, 106 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1951">Miloradovich and Ilina 1951</bibRefCitation>
, pp. 17–20), was revised as Asselian by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mychko, E. V. &amp; Alekseev, A. S." box="[928,1331,1969,1994]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" pagination="40 - 83" refId="ref7190" refString="Mychko, E. V. &amp; Alekseev, A. S. (2017) Localities of middle Carboniferous-Permian trilobites in Russia and surrounding countries. Bulletin of Moscow Society of Naturalists. Geological Series, 92 (3), 40 - 83. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="2017">Mychko and Alekseev (2017, p. 60)</bibRefCitation>
based on the occurrence of the Early Permian foraminiferan 
<taxonomicName authority="(Rauzer-Chernousova, 1936)" authorityName="Rauzer-Chernousova" authorityYear="1936" baseAuthorityName="Rauzer-Chernousova" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[750,1432,2005,2030]" class="Granuloreticulosea" family="Triticitidae" genus="Sphaeroschwagerina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Foraminiferida" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" phylum="Protozoa" rank="species" species="moelleri">
<emphasis box="[750,1089,2005,2030]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="347">Sphaeroschwagerina moelleri</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rauzer-Chernousova, D. M. &amp; Beljaev, G. &amp; Reitlinger, E." box="[1108,1424,2005,2030]" pageId="1" pageNumber="347" pagination="159 - 232" refId="ref7579" refString="Rauzer-Chernousova, D. M., Beljaev, G. &amp; Reitlinger, E. (1936) Upper Paleozoic foraminifera of the Pechora region. Proceedings of the Polar Commission AS SSSR, 28, 159 - 232. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1936">Rauzer-Chernousova, 1936</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hahn, G. &amp; Hahn, R." box="[151,522,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="348" pagination="1 - 242" refId="ref6556" refString="Hahn, G. &amp; Hahn, R. (1996) Die trilobiten-taxa des Karbons und Perms 2. Brachymetopidae. Courier Forschungsinstitut Senckenberg, 195, 1 - 242. [in German]" type="journal article" year="1996">Hahn and Hahn (1996, p. 137)</bibRefCitation>
assigned these specimens to the Carboniferous subspecies 
<taxonomicName authority="ouralicus (de Verneuil, 1845)" authorityName="de Verneuil" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="de Verneuil" baseAuthorityYear="1845" class="Trilobita" family="Brachymetopidae" genus="Brachymetopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Proetida" pageId="2" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ouralicus" subGenus="Conimetopus" subSpecies="ouralicus">
<emphasis box="[1232,1249,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">B</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[1279,1427,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">Conimetopus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[151,368,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">ouralicus ouralicus</emphasis>
(de 
<bibRefCitation author="Verneuil, E. de" box="[419,588,188,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="348" pagination="15 - 396" refId="ref7960" refString="Verneuil, E. de (1845) Terrain Paleozoique. Animaux. In: Murchison, R. I., de Verneuil E. &amp; Keyserling, A. (Eds.), G eologie de la Russie d'Europe et des montagnes de l'Oural. Vol. II. Troiseme partie. Paleontologie. J. Murray, London, Bertrand, Paris, pp. 15 - 396. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 121912" type="book chapter" year="1845">Verneuil, 1845</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Here they are reassigned to 
<taxonomicName authority="Mychko" authorityName="Mychko &amp; Savchuk" authorityYear="2019" box="[919,1329,188,213]" class="Trilobita" family="Brachymetopidae" genus="Brachymetopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Proetida" pageId="2" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alekseevi" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Conimetopus">
<emphasis box="[919,936,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">B</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[959,1107,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">Conimetopus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1124,1226,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">alekseevi</emphasis>
Mychko
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1340,1430,188,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="348" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1340,1430,188,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">
Weber (in 
<bibRefCitation author="Chernov, A. A. &amp; Chernov, G. A." box="[316,646,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="348" refId="ref5996" refString="Chernov, A. A. &amp; Chernov, G. A. (1940) Geologicheskoye stroyeniye basseyna r. Kos'yu v Pechorskom kraye (otchet geologicheskogo otryada Pechorskoy kompleksnoy ekspeditsii SOPS Akademii nauk 1935 g.). AS USSR, Moscow- Leningrad, 103 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1940">Chernov and Chernov [1940]</bibRefCitation>
) identified a trilobite fragment from the Terravean-Kozhim Formation (Early Permian; Asselian; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mychko, E. V. &amp; Alekseev, A. S." box="[452,779,260,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="348" pagination="40 - 83" refId="ref7190" refString="Mychko, E. V. &amp; Alekseev, A. S. (2017) Localities of middle Carboniferous-Permian trilobites in Russia and surrounding countries. Bulletin of Moscow Society of Naturalists. Geological Series, 92 (3), 40 - 83. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="2017">Mychko and Alekseev, 2017</bibRefCitation>
, p. 54) of the Kozhim River in 
<collectingRegion box="[1142,1209,260,285]" country="Russia" name="Komi" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">Komi</collectingRegion>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M'Coy" authorityYear="1847" box="[1221,1395,260,285]" class="Trilobita" family="Brachymetopidae" genus="Brachymetopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Proetida" pageId="2" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1221,1395,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">Brachymetopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. ind. This specimen has never been illustrated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="348" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">
<taxonomicName authority="Licharev" authorityName="Licharev" box="[199,802,332,357]" class="Trilobita" family="Brachymetopidae" genus="Brachymetopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Proetida" pageId="2" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasicus" subGenus="Acutimetopus">
<emphasis box="[199,373,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">Brachymetopus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[394,546,332,355]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">Acutimetopus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[567,690,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">caucasicus</emphasis>
Licharev
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation author="Weber, V. N." box="[856,1004,332,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="348" pagination="1 - 30" refId="ref8123" refString="Weber, V. N. (1944) Trilobity kamennougol'nykh i permskikh otlozheniy SSSR. Vypusk 2. Permskiye trilobity. Monografii popaleontologii SSSR, 1944, 1 - 30. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1944">Weber, 1944</bibRefCitation>
, Pl. 2, Fig. 15; 
<figureCitation box="[1199,1314,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1158,1180]" captionTargetBox="[415,1172,515,1136]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[415,1172,515,1136]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Some members of the genus Brachymetopus from the Permian of Russia. a—B. (Acutimetopus) moelleri (Weber, 1932); reconstruction of cephalon; presumably kept (possibly lost) in the collections of the St. Petersburg Mining University museum, St. Petersburg; Lower Permian, Artinskian, Sarginian (reproduced from Möller [1868, Pl. 1, Fig. 32]). b, c—B. (Conimetopus) alekseevi Mychko, sp. nov.; b—cephalon, spec. TsNIGR no. 5107/2063; c—pygidium, spec. TsNIGR no. 5107/ 2064; Chelyabinsk Region, Ashinsky District, right bank of the Sim River, the town of Asha, “Kazarmenny Kamen” locality; Lower Permian, Asselian; (reproduced from Weber [1937, Pl. 10, figs 10–11]). d, e—B. (Acutimetopus) caucasicus Likharev, 1944; spec. TsNIGR no. 5217/86, holotype, pygidium; Krasnodar Region, Mostovsky District, the Malaya Laba River basin, “Nikitinskaya Balka” locality; Upper Permian, Dzhulfian (~Wuchiapingian), Urushten or Nikitin Formations; d—view from the dorsal side, e—view from the end of the posterior margin (reproduced from Weber [1944, Pl 2, Fig. 15]). The scale bar is 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624469/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">Fig. 1d, e</figureCitation>
herein) is known from a single pygidium from the Northern Caucasus, near the “Nikitinskaya Balka” locality (
<collectingRegion country="Russia" name="Krasnodar" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">Krasnodar Krai</collectingRegion>
, Mostovsky District, the Malaya Laba River basin). In this locality, there are deposits of the Nikitin and Urushten Formations that belong to the Dzhulfian (~Wuchiapingian) of the Upper Permian (
<bibRefCitation author="Kotlyar, G. V. &amp; Zakharov, Y. D. &amp; Kochirkevich, B. V. &amp; Kropacheva, G. S. &amp; Rostovcev, K. O. &amp; Chedia, I. O. &amp; Vuks, G. P. &amp; Guseva, E. A." box="[1196,1424,439,464]" pageId="2" pageNumber="348" refId="ref6738" refString="Kotlyar, G. V., Zakharov, Y. D., Kochirkevich, B. V., Kropacheva, G. S., Rostovcev, K. O., Chedia, I. O., Vuks, G. P. &amp; Guseva, E. A. (1983) Pozdnepermskiy etap evolyutsii organicheskogo mira (Dzhul'finskiy i dorashamskiy yarusy SSSR). Nauka, Leningrad, 200 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1983">
Kotlyar 
<emphasis box="[1292,1356,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">et al.,</emphasis>
1983
</bibRefCitation>
). These are the youngest known members of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M'Coy" authorityYear="1847" box="[752,926,476,501]" class="Trilobita" family="Brachymetopidae" genus="Brachymetopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Proetida" pageId="2" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[752,926,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">Brachymetopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[961,1040,476,501]" name="Russia" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">Russia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
